legacy.full_text: From Long March rockets🚀 to Chang'e lunar projects🌕,  from Tiangong space station 🛰️ to Tianwen-1 Mars mission, I have witnessed dozens of key space missions and programs in China over the past years. Those astonishing and breathtaking moments are always lingering in mind. https://t.co/4ZdL5Wgr8F

legacy.full_text:
There’s a special #cabinet inside #Mengtian lab module which can help taikonauts to do #maintenance work.

It has a mobile platform which can unfold into a plate of 900 millimeters by 700 millimeters, allowing taikonauts to repair large payloads onboard #Tiangong Space Station. https://t.co/fPNPn5qaK4

legacy.full_text:
The 6th China International Import Expo (#CIIE) kicked off on Nov.5 in Shanghai.

The China Aerospace Science and Technology Corporation, or #CASC has brought some models including #ChinaSpaceStation and #Fengyun satellite. Take a look inside the exhibition venue.
(Photo: CASC) https://t.co/zN4thfck9v

legacy.full_text:
A magnetic storm occurred in the night of Nov. 5& morning of Nov. 6, creating rare #auroras in Heilongjiang province & Xinjiang Autonomous Region in #China.
In #Mohe city, the camera captured auroras in red & #green colors.
(Video:Mohe City Converged Media Center) https://t.co/PTRtMfKWDe

legacy.full_text:
What were brought back along with #Shenzhou16 crew?
22 kinds of #samples from 19 scientific experiments, weighing about 25 kilograms. They include life-related samples such as liver cells, proteins, nucleic acids, plants, seeds and microorganisms and the non-life-related samples. https://t.co/qE2nOnjzro

legacy.full_text:
Take a close look at the whole process of #SQX-2Y 's latest flight test.
The launch vehicle used in the test is a single stage, with a 3.35-meter-diameter and a total length of 17 meters. It was powered by a variable thrust JD-1 engine.
(Video: #iSpace) https://t.co/1qzEMY3qoA

legacy.full_text:
#SQX-2Y, a recyclable rocket developed by Chinese  commercial space company #iSpace completed a flight test.
The test stage lifted off from #Jiuquan Satellite Launch Center at 2 p.m. BJT on Nov. 2.  About 1 minute later, it landed smoothly & accurately at the target landing site. https://t.co/H4BjSQDwAU

The three #Shenzhou16 taikonauts, Jing Haipeng, Zhu Yangzhu and Gui Haichao have arrived in Beijing.

They safely returned to Earth on Tuesday after completing their five-month mission.
(Photo Credit: CFP) https://t.co/58DDUjb4Dz

legacy.full_text:
Look,the shining spot at the front is re-entry capsule and the burning trail is propulsion module. 

This was the moment when #Shenzhou16’s re-entry capsule flew across the sky in #Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region early Tuesday morning. 

（Courtesy：@byspto/ @一瞬流光的瞬 ) https://t.co/mxCQJFGnYd
